\id 1CH 13-1CH-kjv.sfm The King James Version of the Holy Bible Wednesday, October 14, 2009
\ide UTF-8
\h 1 Chronicles
\mt The First Book of the Chronicles 
\c 1
\p
\v 1 Adam, Sheth, Enosh, 
\v 2 Kenan, Mahalaleel, Jered, 
\v 3 Henoch, Methuselah, Lamech, 
\v 4 Noah, Shem, Ham, and Japheth.
\p
\v 5 The sons of Japheth; Gomer, and Magog, and Madai, and Javan, and Tubal,
and Meshech, and Tiras. 
\v 6 And the sons of Gomer; Ashchenaz, and Riphath, and Togarmah. 
\v 7 And the sons of Javan; Elishah, and Tarshish, Kittim, and Dodanim.
\p
\v 8 The sons of Ham; Cush, and Mizraim, Put, and Canaan. 
\v 9 And the sons of Cush; Seba, and Havilah, and Sabta, and Raamah, and
Sabtecha. And the sons of Raamah; Sheba, and Dedan. 
\v 10 And Cush begat Nimrod: he began to be mighty upon the earth. 
\v 11 And Mizraim begat Ludim, and Anamim, and Lehabim, and Napthtuhim, 
\v 12 And Pathrusim, and Casluhim, (of whom came the Philistines,) and
Caphthorim. 
\v 13 And Canaan begat Zidon his firstborn, and Heth, 
\v 14 The Jebusite also, and the Amorite, and the Girgashite, 
\v 15 And the Hivite, and the Arkite, and the Sinite, 
\v 16 And the Arvadite, and the Zemarite, and the Hamathite.
\p
\v 17 The sons of Shem; Elam, and Asshur, and Arphaxad, and Lud, and Aram, and
Uz, and Hul, and Gether, and Meshech. 
\v 18 And Arphaxad begat Shelah, and Shelah begat Eber. 
\v 19 And unto Eber were born two sons: the name of the one \add was
\add* Peleg; because in his days the earth was divided: and his brother’s name
\add was\add* Joktan. 
\v 20 And Joktan begat Almodad, and Sheleph, and Hazarmaveth, and Jerah, 
\v 21 Hadoram also, and Uzal, and Diklah, 
\v 22 And Ebal, and Abimael, and Sheba, 
\v 23 And Ophir, and Havilah, and Jobab. All these \add were\add* the sons of
Joktan.
\p
\v 24 Shem, Arphaxad, Shelah, 
\v 25 Eber, Peleg, Reu, 
\v 26 Serug, Nahor, Terah, 
\v 27 Abram; the same \add is\add* Abraham. 
\v 28 The sons of Abraham; Isaac, and Ishmael.
\p
\v 29 These \add are\add* their generations: The firstborn of Ishmael,
Nebaioth; then Kedar, and Adbeel, and Mibsam, 
\v 30 Mishma and Dumah, Massa, Hadad, and Tema, 
\v 31 Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah. These are the sons of Ishmael.
\p
\v 32 Now the sons of Keturah, Abraham’s concubine: she bare Zimran, and
Jokshan, and Medan, and Midian, and Ishbak, and Shuah. And the sons of
Jokshan; Sheba, and Dedan. 
\v 33 And the sons of Midian; Ephah, and Epher, and Henoch, and Abida, and
Eldaah. All these \add are\add* the sons of Keturah. 
\v 34 And Abraham begat Isaac. The sons of Isaac; Esau and Israel.
\p
\v 35 The sons of Esau; Eliphaz, Reuel, and Jeush, and Jaalam, and Korah. 
\v 36 The sons of Eliphaz; Teman, and Omar, Zephi, and Gatam, Kenaz, and
Timna, and Amalek. 
\v 37 The sons of Reuel; Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah. 
\v 38 And the sons of Seir; Lotan, and Shobal, and Zibeon, and Anah, and
Dishon, and Ezar, and Dishan. 
\v 39 And the sons of Lotan; Hori, and Homam: and Timna \add was\add* Lotan’s
sister. 
\v 40 The sons of Shobal; Alian, and Manahath, and Ebal, Shephi, and Onam. And
the sons of Zibeon; Aiah, and Anah. 
\v 41 The sons of Anah; Dishon. And the sons of Dishon; Amram, and Eshban, and
Ithran, and Cheran. 
\v 42 The sons of Ezer; Bilhan, and Zavan, \add and\add* Jakan. The sons of
Dishan; Uz, and Aran.
\p
\v 43 Now these \add are\add* the kings that reigned in the land of Edom
before \add any\add* king reigned over the children of Israel; Bela the son of
Beor: and the name of his city \add was\add* Dinhabah. 
\v 44 And when Bela was dead, Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned in his
stead. 
\v 45 And when Jobab was dead, Husham of the land of the Temanites reigned in
his stead. 
\v 46 And when Husham was dead, Hadad the son of Bedad, which smote Midian in
the field of Moab, reigned in his stead: and the name of his city \add was
\add* Avith. 
\v 47 And when Hadad was dead, Samlah of Masrekah reigned in his stead. 
\v 48 And when Samlah was dead, Shaul of Rehoboth by the river reigned in his
stead. 
\v 49 And when Shaul was dead, Baal-hanan the son of Achbor reigned in his
stead. 
\v 50 And when Baal-hanan was dead, Hadad reigned in his stead: and the name
of his city \add was\add* Pai; and his wife’s name \add was\add* Mehetabel,
the daughter of Matred, the daughter of Mezahab.
\p
\v 51 Hadad died also. And the dukes of Edom were; duke Timnah, duke Aliah,
duke Jetheth, 
\v 52 Duke Aholibamah, duke Elah, duke Pinon, 
\v 53 Duke Kenaz, duke Teman, duke Mibzar, 
\v 54 Duke Magdiel, duke Iram. These \add are\add* the dukes of Edom.
\c 2
\p
\v 1 These \add are\add* the sons of Israel; Reuben, Simeon, Levi, and Judah,
Issachar, and Zebulun, 
\v 2 Dan, Joseph, and Benjamin, Naphtali, Gad, and Asher.
\p
\v 3 The sons of Judah; Er, and Onan, and Shelah: \add which\add* three were
born unto him of the daughter of Shua the Canaanitess. And Er, the firstborn
of Judah, was evil in the sight of the LORD; and he slew him. 
\v 4 And Tamar his daughter in law bare him Pharez and Zerah. All the sons of
Judah \add were\add* five. 
\v 5 The sons of Pharez; Hezron, and Hamul. 
\v 6 And the sons of Zerah; Zimri, and Ethan, and Heman, and Calcol, and Dara:
five of them in all. 
\v 7 And the sons of Carmi; Achar, the troubler of Israel, who transgressed in
the thing accursed. 
\v 8 And the sons of Ethan; Azariah. 
\v 9 The sons also of Hezron, that were born unto him; Jerahmeel, and Ram, and
Chelubai. 
\v 10 And Ram begat Amminadab; and Amminadab begat Nahshon, prince of the
children of Judah; 
\v 11 And Nahshon begat Salma, and Salma begat Boaz, 
\v 12 And Boaz begat Obed, and Obed begat Jesse,
\p
\v 13 And Jesse begat his firstborn Eliab, and Abinadab the second, and Shimma
the third, 
\v 14 Nethaneel the fourth, Raddai the fifth, 
\v 15 Ozem the sixth, David the seventh: 
\v 16 Whose sisters \add were\add* Zeruiah, and Abigail. And the sons of
Zeruiah; Abishai, and Joab, and Asahel, three. 
\v 17 And Abigail bare Amasa: and the father of Amasa \add was\add* Jether the
Ishmeelite.
\p
\v 18 And Caleb the son of Hezron begat \add children\add* of Azubah 
\add his\add* wife, and of Jerioth: her sons \add are\add* these; Jesher, and
Shobab, and Ardon. 
\v 19 And when Azubah was dead, Caleb took unto him Ephrath, which bare him
Hur. 
\v 20 And Hur begat Uri, and Uri begat Bezaleel.
\p
\v 21 And afterward Hezron went in to the daughter of Machir the father of
Gilead, whom he married when he \add was\add* threescore years old; and she
bare him Segub. 
\v 22 And Segub begat Jair, who had three and twenty cities in the land of
Gilead. 
\v 23 And he took Geshur, and Aram, with the towns of Jair, from them, with
Kenath, and the towns thereof, \add even\add* threescore cities. All these 
\add belonged to\add* the sons of Machir the father of Gilead. 
\v 24 And after that Hezron was dead in Caleb-ephratah, then Abiah Hezron’s
wife bare him Ashur the father of Tekoa.
\p
\v 25 And the sons of Jerahmeel the firstborn of Hezron were, Ram the
firstborn, and Bunah, and Oren, and Ozem, \add and\add* Ahijah. 
\v 26 Jerahmeel had also another wife, whose name \add was\add* Atarah; she 
\add was\add* the mother of Onam. 
\v 27 And the sons of Ram the firstborn of Jerahmeel were, Maaz, and Jamin,
and Eker. 
\v 28 And the sons of Onam were, Shammai, and Jada. And the sons of Shammai;
Nadab, and Abishur. 
\v 29 And the name of the wife of Abishur \add was\add* Abihail, and she bare
him Ahban, and Molid. 
\v 30 And the sons of Nadab; Seled, and Appaim: but Seled died without
children. 
\v 31 And the sons of Appaim; Ishi. And the sons of Ishi; Sheshan. And the
children of Sheshan; Ahlai. 
\v 32 And the sons of Jada the brother of Shammai; Jether and Jonathan: and
Jether died without children. 
\v 33 And the sons of Jonathan; Peleth, and Zaza. These were the sons of
Jerahmeel.
\p
\v 34 Now Sheshan had no sons, but daughters. And Sheshan had a servant, an
Egyptian, whose name \add was\add* Jarha. 
\v 35 And Sheshan gave his daughter to Jarha his servant to wife; and she bare
him Attai. 
\v 36 And Attai begat Nathan, and Nathan begat Zabad, 
\v 37 And Zabad begat Ephlal, and Ephlal begat Obed, 
\v 38 And Obed begat Jehu, and Jehu begat Azariah, 
\v 39 And Azariah begat Helez, and Helez begat Eleasah, 
\v 40 And Eleasah begat Sisamai, and Sisamai begat Shallum, 
\v 41 And Shallum begat Jekamiah, and Jekamiah begat Elishama.
\p
\v 42 Now the sons of Caleb the brother of Jerahmeel \add were,\add* Mesha his
firstborn, which was the father of Ziph; and the sons of Mareshah the father
of Hebron. 
\v 43 And the sons of Hebron; Korah, and Tappuah, and Rekem, and Shema. 
\v 44 And Shema begat Raham, the father of Jorkoam: and Rekem begat Shammai. 
\v 45 And the son of Shammai \add was\add* Maon: and Maon \add was\add* the
father of Beth-zur. 
\v 46 And Ephah, Caleb’s concubine, bare Haran, and Moza, and Gazez: and Haran
begat Gazez. 
\v 47 And the sons of Jahdai; Regem, and Jotham, and Gesham, and Pelet, and
Ephah, and Shaaph. 
\v 48 Maachah, Caleb’s concubine, bare Sheber, and Tirhanah. 
\v 49 She bare also Shaaph the father of Madmannah, Sheva the father of
Machbenah, and the father of Gibea: and the daughter of Caleb \add was
\add* Achsa.
\p
\v 50 These were the sons of Caleb the son of Hur, the firstborn of Ephratah;
Shobal the father of Kirjath-jearim, 
\v 51 Salma the father of Bethlehem, Hareph the father of Beth- gader. 
\v 52 And Shobal the father of Kirjath-jearim had sons; Haroeh, \add and
\add* half of the Manahethites. 
\v 53 And the families of Kirjath-jearim; the Ithrites, and the Puhites, and
the Shumathites, and the Mishraites; of them came the Zareathites, and the
Eshtaulites. 
\v 54 The sons of Salma; Bethlehem, and the Netophathites, Ataroth, the house
of Joab, and half of the Manahethites, the Zorites. 
\v 55 And the families of the scribes which dwelt at Jabez; the Tirathites,
the Shimeathites, \add and\add* Suchathites. These \add are\add* the Kenites
that came of Hemath, the father of the house of Rechab.
\c 3
\p
\v 1 Now these were the sons of David, which were born unto him in Hebron; the
firstborn Amnon, of Ahinoam the Jezreelitess; the second Daniel, of Abigail
the Carmelitess: 
\v 2 The third, Absalom the son of Maachah the daughter of Talmai king of
Geshur: the fourth, Adonijah the son of Haggith: 
\v 3 The fifth, Shephatiah of Abital: the sixth, Ithream by Eglah his wife. 
\v 4 \add These\add* six were born unto him in Hebron; and there he reigned
seven years and six months: and in Jerusalem he reigned thirty and three
years. 
\v 5 And these were born unto him in Jerusalem; Shimea, and Shobab, and
Nathan, and Solomon, four, of Bath-shua the daughter of Ammiel: 
\v 6 Ibhar also, and Elishama, and Eliphelet, 
\v 7 And Nogah, and Nepheg, and Japhia, 
\v 8 And Elishama, and Eliada, and Eliphelet, nine. 
\v 9 \add These were\add* all the sons of David, beside the sons of the
concubines, and Tamar their sister.
\p
\v 10 And Solomon’s son \add was\add* Rehoboam, Abia his son, Asa his son,
Jehoshaphat his son, 
\v 11 Joram his son, Ahaziah his son, Joash his son, 
\v 12 Amaziah his son, Azariah his son, Jotham his son, 
\v 13 Ahaz his son, Hezekiah his son, Manasseh his son, 
\v 14 Amon his son, Josiah his son. 
\v 15 And the sons of Josiah \add were,\add* the firstborn Johanan, the second
Jehoiakim, the third Zedekiah, the fourth Shallum. 
\v 16 And the sons of Jehoiakim: Jeconiah his son, Zedekiah his son.
\p
\v 17 And the sons of Jeconiah; Assir, Salathiel his son, 
\v 18 Malchiram also, and Pedaiah, and Shenazar, Jecamiah, Hoshama, and
Nedabiah. 
\v 19 And the sons of Pedaiah \add were,\add* Zerubbabel, and Shimei: and the
sons of Zerubbabel; Meshullam, and Hananiah, and Shelomith their sister: 
\v 20 And Hashubah, and Ohel, and Berechiah, and Hasadiah, Jushab-hesed,
five. 
\v 21 And the sons of Hananiah; Pelatiah, and Jesaiah: the sons of Rephaiah,
the sons of Arnan, the sons of Obadiah, the sons of Shechaniah. 
\v 22 And the sons of Shechaniah; Shemaiah; and the sons of Shemaiah; Hattush,
and Igeal, and Bariah, and Neariah, and Shaphat, six. 
\v 23 And the sons of Neariah; Elioenai, and Hezekiah, and Azrikam, three. 
\v 24 And the sons of Elioenai \add were,\add* Hodaiah, and Eliashib, and
Pelaiah, and Akkub, and Johanan, and Dalaiah, and Anani, seven.
\c 4
\p
\v 1 The sons of Judah; Pharez, Hezron, and Carmi, and Hur, and Shobal. 
\v 2 And Reaiah the son of Shobal begat Jahath; and Jahath begat Ahumai and
Lahad. These \add are\add* the families of the Zorathites. 
\v 3 And these \add were of\add* the father of Etam; Jezreel, and Ishma, and
Idbash: and the name of their sister \add was\add* Hazelelponi: 
\v 4 And Penuel the father of Gedor and Ezer the father of Hushah. These 
\add are\add* the sons of Hur, the firstborn of Ephratah, the father of
Bethlehem.
\p
\v 5 And Ashur the father of Tekoa had two wives, Helah and Naarah. 
\v 6 And Naarah bare him Ahuzam, and Hepher, and Temeni, and Haahashtari.
These \add were\add* the sons of Naarah. 
\v 7 And the sons of Helah \add were,\add* Zereth, and Jezoar, and Ethnan. 
\v 8 And Coz begat Anub, and Zobebah, and the families of Aharhel the son of
Harum.
\p
\v 9 And Jabez was more honourable than his brethren: and his mother called
his name Jabez, saying, Because I bare him with sorrow. 
\v 10 And Jabez called on the God of Israel, saying, Oh that thou wouldest
bless me indeed, and enlarge my coast, and that thine hand might be with me,
and that thou wouldest keep \add me\add* from evil, that it may not grieve me!
And God granted him that which he requested.
\p
\v 11 And Chelub the brother of Shuah begat Mehir, which \add was\add* the
father of Eshton. 
\v 12 And Eshton begat Beth-rapha, and Paseah, and Tehinnah the father of
Ir-nahash. These \add are\add* the men of Rechah. 
\v 13 And the sons of Kenaz; Othniel, and Seraiah: and the sons of Othniel;
Hathath. 
\v 14 And Meonothai begat Ophrah: and Seraiah begat Joab, the father of the
valley of Charashim; for they were craftsmen. 
\v 15 And the sons of Caleb the son of Jephunneh; Iru, Elah, and Naam: and the
sons of Elah, even Kenaz. 
\v 16 And the sons of Jehaleleel; Ziph, and Ziphah, Tiria, and Asareel. 
\v 17 And the sons of Ezra \add were,\add* Jether, and Mered, and Epher, and
Jalon: and she bare Miriam, and Shammai, and Ishbah the father of Eshtemoa. 
\v 18 And his wife Jehudijah bare Jered the father of Gedor, and Heber the
father of Socho, and Jekuthiel the father of Zanoah. And these \add are
\add* the sons of Bithiah the daughter of Pharaoh, which Mered took. 
\v 19 And the sons of \add his\add* wife Hodiah the sister of Naham, the
father of Keilah the Garmite, and Eshtemoa the Maachathite. 
\v 20 And the sons of Shimon \add were,\add* Amnon, and Rinnah, Ben-hanan, and
Tilon. And the sons of Ishi \add were,\add* Zoheth, and Ben-zoheth.
\p
\v 21 The sons of Shelah the son of Judah \add were,\add* Er the father of
Lecah, and Laadah the father of Mareshah, and the families of the house of
them that wrought fine linen, of the house of Ashbea, 
\v 22 And Jokim, and the men of Chozeba, and Joash, and Saraph, who had the
dominion in Moab, and Jashubi-lehem. And \add these are\add* ancient things. 
\v 23 These \add were\add* the potters, and those that dwelt among plants and
hedges: there they dwelt with the king for his work.
\p
\v 24 The sons of Simeon \add were,\add* Nemuel, and Jamin, Jarib, Zerah, 
\add and\add* Shaul: 
\v 25 Shallum his son, Mibsam his son, Mishma his son. 
\v 26 And the sons of Mishma; Hamuel his son, Zacchur his son, Shimei his
son. 
\v 27 And Shimei had sixteen sons and six daughters; but his brethren had not
many children, neither did all their family multiply, like to the children of
Judah. 
\v 28 And they dwelt at Beer-sheba, and Moladah, and Hazar-shual, 
\v 29 And at Bilhah, and at Ezem, and at Tolad, 
\v 30 And at Bethuel, and at Hormah, and at Ziklag, 
\v 31 And at Beth-marcaboth, and Hazar-susim, and at Beth- birei, and at
Shaaraim. These \add were\add* their cities unto the reign of David. 
\v 32 And their villages \add were,\add* Etam, and Ain, Rimmon, and Tochen,
and Ashan, five cities: 
\v 33 And all their villages that \add were\add* round about the same cities,
unto Baal. These \add were\add* their habitations, and their genealogy. 
\v 34 And Meshobab, and Jamlech, and Joshah the son of Amaziah, 
\v 35 And Joel, and Jehu the son of Josibiah, the son of Seraiah, the son of
Asiel, 
\v 36 And Elioenai, and Jaakobah, and Jeshohaiah, and Asaiah, and Adiel, and
Jesimiel, and Benaiah, 
\v 37 And Ziza the son of Shiphi, the son of Allon, the son of Jedaiah, the
son of Shimri, the son of Shemaiah; 
\v 38 These mentioned by \add their\add* names \add were\add* princes in their
families: and the house of their fathers increased greatly.
\p
\v 39 And they went to the entrance of Gedor, \add even\add* unto the east
side of the valley, to seek pasture for their flocks. 
\v 40 And they found fat pasture and good, and the land \add was\add* wide,
and quiet, and peaceable; for \add they\add* of Ham had dwelt there of old. 
\v 41 And these written by name came in the days of Hezekiah king of Judah,
and smote their tents, and the habitations that were found there, and
destroyed them utterly unto this day, and dwelt in their rooms: because 
\add there was\add* pasture there for their flocks. 
\v 42 And \add some\add* of them, \add even\add* of the sons of Simeon, five
hundred men, went to mount Seir, having for their captains Pelatiah, and
Neariah, and Rephaiah, and Uzziel, the sons of Ishi. 
\v 43 And they smote the rest of the Amalekites that were escaped, and dwelt
there unto this day.
\c 5
\p
\v 1 Now the sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel, (for he \add was
\add* the firstborn; but, forasmuch as he defiled his father’s bed, his
birthright was given unto the sons of Joseph the son of Israel: and the
genealogy is not to be reckoned after the birthright. 
\v 2 For Judah prevailed above his brethren, and of him \add came\add* the
chief ruler; but the birthright \add was\add* Joseph’s:) 
\v 3 The sons, \add I say,\add* of Reuben the firstborn of Israel \add were,
\add* Hanoch, and Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi. 
\v 4 The sons of Joel; Shemaiah his son, Gog his son, Shimei his son, 
\v 5 Micah his son, Reaia his son, Baal his son, 
\v 6 Beerah his son, whom Tilgath-pilneser king of Assyria carried away 
\add captive:\add* he \add was\add* prince of the Reubenites. 
\v 7 And his brethren by their families, when the genealogy of their
generations was reckoned, \add were\add* the chief, Jeiel, and Zechariah, 
\v 8 And Bela the son of Azaz, the son of Shema, the son of Joel, who dwelt in
Aroer, even unto Nebo and Baal-meon: 
\v 9 And eastward he inhabited unto the entering in of the wilderness from the
river Euphrates: because their cattle were multiplied in the \add land
\add* of Gilead. 
\v 10 And in the days of Saul they made war with the Hagarites, who fell by
their hand: and they dwelt in their tents throughout all the east land of
Gilead.
\p
\v 11 And the children of Gad dwelt over against them, in the land of Bashan
unto Salchah: 
\v 12 Joel the chief, and Shapham the next, and Jaanai, and Shaphat in
Bashan. 
\v 13 And their brethren of the house of their fathers \add were,\add*
Michael, and Meshullam, and Sheba, and Jorai, and Jachan, and Zia, and Heber,
seven. 
\v 14 These \add are\add* the children of Abihail the son of Huri, the son of
Jaroah, the son of Gilead, the son of Michael, the son of Jeshishai, the son
of Jahdo, the son of Buz; 
\v 15 Ahi the son of Abdiel, the son of Guni, chief of the house of their
fathers. 
\v 16 And they dwelt in Gilead in Bashan, and in her towns, and in all the
suburbs of Sharon, upon their borders. 
\v 17 All these were reckoned by genealogies in the days of Jotham king of
Judah, and in the days of Jeroboam king of Israel.
\p
\v 18 The sons of Reuben, and the Gadites, and half the tribe of Manasseh, of
valiant men, men able to bear buckler and sword, and to shoot with bow, and
skilful in war, \add were\add* four and forty thousand seven hundred and
threescore, that went out to the war. 
\v 19 And they made war with the Hagarites, with Jetur, and Nephish, and
Nodab. 
\v 20 And they were helped against them, and the Hagarites were delivered into
their hand, and all that \add were\add* with them: for they cried to God in
the battle, and he was intreated of them; because they put their trust in
him. 
\v 21 And they took away their cattle; of their camels fifty thousand, and of
sheep two hundred and fifty thousand, and of asses two thousand, and of men an
hundred thousand. 
\v 22 For there fell down many slain, because the war \add was\add* of God.
And they dwelt in their steads until the captivity.
\p
\v 23 And the children of the half tribe of Manasseh dwelt in the land: they
increased from Bashan unto Baal-hermon and Senir, and unto mount Hermon. 
\v 24 And these \add were\add* the heads of the house of their fathers, even
Epher, and Ishi, and Eliel, and Azriel, and Jeremiah, and Hodaviah, and
Jahdiel, mighty men of valour, famous men, \add and\add* heads of the house of
their fathers.
\p
\v 25 And they transgressed against the God of their fathers, and went a
whoring after the gods of the people of the land, whom God destroyed before
them. 
\v 26 And the God of Israel stirred up the spirit of Pul king of Assyria, and
the spirit of Tilgath-pilneser king of Assyria, and he carried them away, even
the Reubenites, and the Gadites, and the half tribe of Manasseh, and brought
them unto Halah, and Habor, and Hara, and to the river Gozan, unto this day.
\c 6
\p
\v 1 The sons of Levi; Gershon, Kohath, and Merari. 
\v 2 And the sons of Kohath; Amram, Izhar, and Hebron, and Uzziel. 
\v 3 And the children of Amram; Aaron, and Moses, and Miriam. The sons also of
Aaron; Nadab, and Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.
\p
\v 4 Eleazar begat Phinehas, Phinehas begat Abishua, 
\v 5 And Abishua begat Bukki, and Bukki begat Uzzi, 
\v 6 And Uzzi begat Zerahiah, and Zerahiah begat Meraioth, 
\v 7 Meraioth begat Amariah, and Amariah begat Ahitub, 
\v 8 And Ahitub begat Zadok, and Zadok begat Ahimaaz, 
\v 9 And Ahimaaz begat Azariah, and Azariah begat Johanan, 
\v 10 And Johanan begat Azariah, (he \add it is\add* that executed the
priest’s office in the temple that Solomon built in Jerusalem:) 
\v 11 And Azariah begat Amariah, and Amariah begat Ahitub, 
\v 12 And Ahitub begat Zadok, and Zadok begat Shallum, 
\v 13 And Shallum begat Hilkiah, and Hilkiah begat Azariah, 
\v 14 And Azariah begat Seraiah, and Seraiah begat Jehozadak, 
\v 15 And Jehozadak went \add into captivity,\add* when the LORD carried away
Judah and Jerusalem by the hand of Nebuchadnezzar.
\p
\v 16 The sons of Levi; Gershom, Kohath, and Merari. 
\v 17 And these \add be\add* the names of the sons of Gershom; Libni, and
Shimei. 
\v 18 And the sons of Kohath \add were,\add* Amram, and Izhar, and Hebron, and
Uzziel. 
\v 19 The sons of Merari; Mahli, and Mushi. And these \add are\add* the
families of the Levites according to their fathers. 
\v 20 Of Gershom; Libni his son, Jahath his son, Zimmah his son, 
\v 21 Joah his son, Iddo his son, Zerah his son, Jeaterai his son. 
\v 22 The sons of Kohath; Amminadab his son, Korah his son, Assir his son, 
\v 23 Elkanah his son, and Ebiasaph his son, and Assir his son, 
\v 24 Tahath his son, Uriel his son, Uzziah his son, and Shaul his son. 
\v 25 And the sons of Elkanah; Amasai, and Ahimoth. 
\v 26 \add As for\add* Elkanah: the sons of Elkanah; Zophai his son, and
Nahath his son, 
\v 27 Eliab his son, Jeroham his son, Elkanah his son. 
\v 28 And the sons of Samuel; the firstborn Vashni, and Abiah. 
\v 29 The sons of Merari; Mahli, Libni his son, Shimei his son, Uzza his son,
\v 30 Shimea his son, Haggiah his son, Asaiah his son. 
\v 31 And these \add are they\add* whom David set over the service of song in
the house of the LORD, after that the ark had rest. 
\v 32 And they ministered before the dwelling place of the tabernacle of the
congregation with singing, until Solomon had built the house of the LORD in
Jerusalem: and \add then\add* they waited on their office according to their
order. 
\v 33 And these \add are\add* they that waited with their children. Of the
sons of the Kohathites: Heman a singer, the son of Joel, the son of Shemuel, 
\v 34 The son of Elkanah, the son of Jeroham, the son of Eliel, the son of
Toah, 
\v 35 The son of Zuph, the son of Elkanah, the son of Mahath, the son of
Amasai, 
\v 36 The son of Elkanah, the son of Joel, the son of Azariah, the son of
Zephaniah, 
\v 37 The son of Tahath, the son of Assir, the son of Ebiasaph, the son of
Korah, 
\v 38 The son of Izhar, the son of Kohath, the son of Levi, the son of
Israel. 
\v 39 And his brother Asaph, who stood on his right hand, \add even
\add* Asaph the son of Berachiah, the son of Shimea, 
\v 40 The son of Michael, the son of Baaseiah, the son of Malchiah, 
\v 41 The son of Ethni, the son of Zerah, the son of Adaiah, 
\v 42 The son of Ethan, the son of Zimmah, the son of Shimei, 
\v 43 The son of Jahath, the son of Gershom, the son of Levi. 
\v 44 And their brethren the sons of Merari \add stood\add* on the left hand:
Ethan the son of Kishi, the son of Abdi, the son of Malluch, 
\v 45 The son of Hashabiah, the son of Amaziah, the son of Hilkiah, 
\v 46 The son of Amzi, the son of Bani, the son of Shamer, 
\v 47 The son of Mahli, the son of Mushi, the son of Merari, the son of Levi.
\v 48 Their brethren also the Levites \add were\add* appointed unto all manner
of service of the tabernacle of the house of God.
\p
\v 49 But Aaron and his sons offered upon the altar of the burnt offering, and
on the altar of incense, \add and were appointed\add* for all the work of the
\add place\add* most holy, and to make an atonement for Israel, according to
all that Moses the servant of God had commanded. 
\v 50 And these \add are\add* the sons of Aaron; Eleazar his son, Phinehas his
son, Abishua his son, 
\v 51 Bukki his son, Uzzi his son, Zerahiah his son, 
\v 52 Meraioth his son, Amariah his son, Ahitub his son, 
\v 53 Zadok his son, Ahimaaz his son.
\p
\v 54 Now these \add are\add* their dwelling places throughout their castles
in their coasts, of the sons of Aaron, of the families of the Kohathites: for
theirs was the lot. 
\v 55 And they gave them Hebron in the land of Judah, and the suburbs thereof
round about it. 
\v 56 But the fields of the city, and the villages thereof, they gave to Caleb
the son of Jephunneh. 
\v 57 And to the sons of Aaron they gave the cities of Judah, \add namely,
\add* Hebron, \add the city\add* of refuge, and Libnah with her suburbs, and
Jattir, and Eshtemoa, with their suburbs, 
\v 58 And Hilen with her suburbs, Debir with her suburbs, 
\v 59 And Ashan with her suburbs, and Beth-shemesh with her suburbs: 
\v 60 And out of the tribe of Benjamin; Geba with her suburbs, and Alemeth
with her suburbs, and Anathoth with her suburbs. All their cities throughout
their families \add were\add* thirteen cities. 
\v 61 And unto the sons of Kohath, \add which were\add* left of the family of
that tribe, \add were cities given\add* out of the half tribe, \add namely,
out of\add* the half \add tribe\add* of Manasseh, by lot, ten cities. 
\v 62 And to the sons of Gershom throughout their families out of the tribe of
Issachar, and out of the tribe of Asher, and out of the tribe of Naphtali, and
out of the tribe of Manasseh in Bashan, thirteen cities. 
\v 63 Unto the sons of Merari \add were given\add* by lot, throughout their
families, out of the tribe of Reuben, and out of the tribe of Gad, and out of
the tribe of Zebulun, twelve cities. 
\v 64 And the children of Israel gave to the Levites \add these\add* cities
with their suburbs. 
\v 65 And they gave by lot out of the tribe of the children of Judah, and out
of the tribe of the children of Simeon, and out of the tribe of the children
of Benjamin, these cities, which are called by \add their\add* names. 
\v 66 And \add the residue\add* of the families of the sons of Kohath had
cities of their coasts out of the tribe of Ephraim. 
\v 67 And they gave unto them, \add of\add* the cities of refuge, Shechem in
mount Ephraim with her suburbs; \add they gave\add* also Gezer with her
suburbs, 
\v 68 And Jokmeam with her suburbs, and Beth-horon with her suburbs, 
\v 69 And Aijalon with her suburbs, and Gath- rimmon with her suburbs: 
\v 70 And out of the half tribe of Manasseh; Aner with her suburbs, and Bileam
with her suburbs, for the family of the remnant of the sons of Kohath. 
\v 71 Unto the sons of Gershom \add were given\add* out of the family of the
half tribe of Manasseh, Golan in Bashan with her suburbs, and Ashtaroth with
her suburbs: 
\v 72 And out of the tribe of Issachar; Kedesh with her suburbs, Daberath with
her suburbs, 
\v 73 And Ramoth with her suburbs, and Anem with her suburbs: 
\v 74 And out of the tribe of Asher; Mashal with her suburbs, and Abdon with
her suburbs, 
\v 75 And Hukok with her suburbs, and Rehob with her suburbs: 
\v 76 And out of the tribe of Naphtali; Kedesh in Galilee with her suburbs,
and Hammon with her suburbs, and Kirjathaim with her suburbs. 
\v 77 Unto the rest of the children of Merari \add were given\add* out of the
tribe of Zebulun. Rimmon with her suburbs, Tabor with her suburbs: 
\v 78 And on the other side Jordan by Jericho, on the east side of Jordan, 
\add were given them\add* out of the tribe of Reuben, Bezer in the wilderness
with her suburbs, and Jahzah with her suburbs, 
\v 79 Kedemoth also with her suburbs, and Mephaath with her suburbs: 
\v 80 And out of the tribe of Gad; Ramoth in Gilead with her suburbs, and
Mahanaim with her suburbs, 
\v 81 And Heshbon with her suburbs, and Jazer with her suburbs.
\c 7
\p
\v 1 Now the sons of Issachar \add were,\add* Tola, and Puah, Jashub, and
Shimrom, four. 
\v 2 And the sons of Tola; Uzzi, and Rephaiah, and Jeriel, and Jahmai, and
Jibsam, and Shemuel, heads of their father’s house, \add to wit,\add* of Tola:
\add they were\add* valiant men of might in their generations; whose number 
\add was\add* in the days of David two and twenty thousand and six hundred. 
\v 3 And the sons of Uzzi; Izrahiah: and the sons of Izrahiah; Michael, and
Obadiah, and Joel, Ishiah, five: all of them chief men. 
\v 4 And with them, by their generations, after the house of their fathers, 
\add were\add* bands of soldiers for war, six and thirty thousand \add men:
\add* for they had many wives and sons. 
\v 5 And their brethren among all the families of Issachar \add were
\add* valiant men of might, reckoned in all by their genealogies fourscore and
seven thousand.
\p
\v 6 \add The sons\add* of Benjamin; Bela, and Becher, and Jediael, three. 
\v 7 And the sons of Bela; Ezbon, and Uzzi, and Uzziel, and Jerimoth, and Iri,
five; heads of the house of \add their\add* fathers, mighty men of valour; and
were reckoned by their genealogies twenty and two thousand and thirty and
four. 
\v 8 And the sons of Becher; Zemira, and Joash, and Eliezer, and Elioenai, and
Omri, and Jerimoth, and Abiah, and Anathoth, and Alameth. All these 
\add are\add* the sons of Becher. 
\v 9 And the number of them, after their genealogy by their generations, heads
of the house of the fathers, mighty men of valour, \add was\add* twenty
thousand and two hundred. 
\v 10 The sons also of Jediael; Bilhan: and the sons of Bilhan; Jeush, and
Benjamin, and Ehud, and Chenaanah, and Zethan, and Tharshish, and Ahishahar. 
\v 11 All these the sons of Jediael, by the heads of their fathers, mighty men
of valour, \add were\add* seventeen thousand and two hundred \add soldiers,
\add* fit to go out for war \add and\add* battle. 
\v 12 Shuppim also, and Huppim, the children of Ir, \add and\add* Hushim, the
sons of Aher.
\p
\v 13 The sons of Naphtali; Jahziel, and Guni, and Jezer, and Shallum, the
sons of Bilhah.
\p
\v 14 The sons of Manasseh; Ashriel, whom she bare: \add (but\add* his
concubine the Aramitess bare Machir the father of Gilead: 
\v 15 And Machir took to wife \add the sister\add* of Huppim and Shuppim,
whose sister’s name \add was\add* Maachah;) and the name of the second 
\add was\add* Zelophehad: and Zelophehad had daughters. 
\v 16 And Maachah the wife of Machir bare a son, and she called his name
Peresh; and the name of his brother \add was\add* Sheresh; and his sons 
\add were\add* Ulam and Rakem. 
\v 17 And the sons of Ulam; Bedan. These \add were\add* the sons of Gilead,
the son of Machir, the son of Manasseh. 
\v 18 And his sister Hammoleketh bare Ishod, and Abiezer, and Mahalah. 
\v 19 And the sons of Shemidah were, Ahian, and Shechem, and Likhi, and
Aniam.
\p
\v 20 And the sons of Ephraim; Shuthelah, and Bered his son, and Tahath his
son, and Eladah his son, and Tahath his son,
\p
\v 21 And Zabad his son, and Shuthelah his son, and Ezer, and Elead, whom the
men of Gath \add that were\add* born in \add that\add* land slew, because they
came down to take away their cattle. 
\v 22 And Ephraim their father mourned many days, and his brethren came to
comfort him.
\p
\v 23 And when he went in to his wife, she conceived, and bare a son, and he
called his name Beriah, because it went evil with his house. 
\v 24 (And his daughter \add was\add* Sherah, who built Beth-horon the nether,
and the upper, and Uzzen-sherah.) 
\v 25 And Rephah \add was\add* his son, also Resheph, and Telah his son, and
Tahan his son, 
\v 26 Laadan his son, Ammihud his son, Elishama his son, 
\v 27 Non his son, Jehoshuah his son.
\p
\v 28 And their possessions and habitations \add were,\add* Bethel and the
towns thereof, and eastward Naaran, and westward Gezer, with the towns
thereof; Shechem also and the towns thereof, unto Gaza and the towns thereof:
\v 29 And by the borders of the children of Manasseh, Beth-shean and her
towns, Taanach and her towns, Megiddo and her towns, Dor and her towns. In
these dwelt the children of Joseph the son of Israel.
\p
\v 30 The sons of Asher; Imnah, and Isuah, and Ishuai, and Beriah, and Serah
their sister. 
\v 31 And the sons of Beriah; Heber, and Malchiel, who \add is\add* the father
of Birzavith. 
\v 32 And Heber begat Japhlet, and Shomer, and Hotham, and Shua their sister.
\v 33 And the sons of Japhlet; Pasach, and Bimhal, and Ashvath. These 
\add are\add* the children of Japhlet. 
\v 34 And the sons of Shamer; Ahi, and Rohgah, Jehubbah, and Aram. 
\v 35 And the sons of his brother Helem; Zophah, and Imna, and Shelesh, and
Amal. 
\v 36 The sons of Zophah; Suah, and Harnepher, and Shual, and Beri, and
Imrah, 
\v 37 Bezer, and Hod, and Shamma and Shilshah, and Ithran, and Beera. 
\v 38 And the sons of Jether; Jephunneh, and Pispah, and Ara. 
\v 39 And the sons of Ulla; Arah, and Haniel, and Rezia. 
\v 40 All these \add were\add* the children of Asher, heads of \add their
\add* father’s house, choice \add and\add* mighty men of valour, chief of the
princes. And the number throughout the genealogy of them that were apt to the
war \add and\add* to battle \add was\add* twenty and six thousand men.
\c 8
\p
\v 1 Now Benjamin begat Bela his firstborn, Ashbel the second, and Aharah the
third, 
\v 2 Nohah the fourth, and Rapha the fifth. 
\v 3 And the sons of Bela were, Addar, and Gera, and Abihud, 
\v 4 And Abishua, and Naaman, and Ahoah, 
\v 5 And Gera, and Shephuphan, and Huram. 
\v 6 And these \add are\add* the sons of Ehud: these are the heads of the
fathers of the inhabitants of Geba, and they removed them to Manahath: 
\v 7 And Naaman, and Ahiah, and Gera, he removed them, and begat Uzza, and
Ahihud. 
\v 8 And Shaharaim begat \add children\add* in the country of Moab, after he
had sent them away; Hushim and Baara \add were\add* his wives. 
\v 9 And he begat of Hodesh his wife, Jobab, and Zibia, and Mesha, and
Malcham, 
\v 10 And Jeuz, and Shachia, and Mirma. These \add were\add* his sons, heads
of the fathers. 
\v 11 And of Hushim he begat Abitub, and Elpaal. 
\v 12 The sons of Elpaal; Eber, and Misham, and Shamed, who built Ono, and
Lod, with the towns thereof: 
\v 13 Beriah also, and Shema, who \add were\add* heads of the fathers of the
inhabitants of Aijalon, who drove away the inhabitants of Gath: 
\v 14 And Ahio, Shashak, and Jeremoth, 
\v 15 And Zebadiah, and Arad, and Ader, 
\v 16 And Michael, and Ispah, and Joha, the sons of Beriah; 
\v 17 And Zebadiah, and Meshullam, and Hezeki, and Heber, 
\v 18 Ishmerai also, and Jezliah, and Jobab, the sons of Elpaal; 
\v 19 And Jakim, and Zichri, and Zabdi, 
\v 20 And Elienai, and Zilthai, and Eliel, 
\v 21 And Adaiah, and Beraiah, and Shimrath, the sons of Shimhi; 
\v 22 And Ishpan, and Heber, and Eliel, 
\v 23 And Abdon, and Zichri, and Hanan, 
\v 24 And Hananiah, and Elam, and Antothijah, 
\v 25 And Iphedeiah, and Penuel, the sons of Shashak; 
\v 26 And Shamsherai, and Shehariah, and Athaliah, 
\v 27 And Jaresiah, and Eliah, and Zichri, the sons of Jeroham. 
\v 28 These \add were\add* heads of the fathers, by their generations, chief 
\add men.\add* These dwelt in Jerusalem. 
\v 29 And at Gibeon dwelt the father of Gibeon; whose wife’s name \add was
\add* Maachah: 
\v 30 And his firstborn son Abdon, and Zur, and Kish, and Baal, and Nadab, 
\v 31 And Gedor, and Ahio, and Zacher. 
\v 32 And Mikloth begat Shimeah. And these also dwelt with their brethren in
Jerusalem, over against them.
\p
\v 33 And Ner begat Kish, and Kish begat Saul, and Saul begat Jonathan, and
Malchi- shua, and Abinadab, and Esh-baal. 
\v 34 And the son of Jonathan \add was\add* Merib-baal; and Merib-baal begat
Micah. 
\v 35 And the sons of Micah \add were,\add* Pithon, and Melech, and Tarea, and
Ahaz. 
\v 36 And Ahaz begat Jehoadah; and Jehoadah begat Alemeth, and Azmaveth, and
Zimri; and Zimri begat Moza, 
\v 37 And Moza begat Binea: Rapha \add was\add* his son, Eleasah his son, Azel
his son: 
\v 38 And Azel had six sons, whose names \add are\add* these, Azrikam,
Bocheru, and Ishmael, and Sheariah, and Obadiah, and Hanan. All these 
\add were\add* the sons of Azel. 
\v 39 And the sons of Eshek his brother \add were,\add* Ulam his firstborn,
Jehush the second, and Eliphelet the third. 
\v 40 And the sons of Ulam were mighty men of valour, archers, and had many
sons, and sons’ sons, an hundred and fifty. All these \add are\add* of the
sons of Benjamin.
\c 9
\p
\v 1 So all Israel were reckoned by genealogies; and, behold, they \add were
\add* written in the book of the kings of Israel and Judah, \add who
\add* were carried away to Babylon for their transgression.
\p
\v 2 Now the first inhabitants that \add dwelt\add* in their possessions in
their cities \add were,\add* the Israelites, the priests, Levites, and the
Nethinims. 
\v 3 And in Jerusalem dwelt of the children of Judah, and of the children of
Benjamin, and of the children of Ephraim, and Manasseh; 
\v 4 Uthai the son of Ammihud, the son of Omri, the son of Imri, the son of
Bani, of the children of Pharez the son of Judah. 
\v 5 And of the Shilonites; Asaiah the firstborn, and his sons. 
\v 6 And of the sons of Zerah; Jeuel, and their brethren, six hundred and
ninety. 
\v 7 And of the sons of Benjamin; Sallu the son of Meshullam, the son of
Hodaviah, the son of Hasenuah, 
\v 8 And Ibneiah the son of Jeroham, and Elah the son of Uzzi, the son of
Michri, and Meshullam the son of Shephatiah, the son of Reuel, the son of
Ibnijah; 
\v 9 And their brethren, according to their generations, nine hundred and
fifty and six. All these men \add were\add* chief of the fathers in the house
of their fathers.
\p
\v 10 And of the priests; Jedaiah, and Jehoiarib, and Jachin, 
\v 11 And Azariah the son of Hilkiah, the son of Meshullam, the son of Zadok,
the son of Meraioth, the son of Ahitub, the ruler of the house of God; 
\v 12 And Adaiah the son of Jeroham, the son of Pashur, the son of Malchijah,
and Maasiai the son of Adiel, the son of Jahzerah, the son of Meshullam, the
son of Meshillemith, the son of Immer; 
\v 13 And their brethren, heads of the house of their fathers, a thousand and
seven hundred and threescore; very able men for the work of the service of the
house of God. 
\v 14 And of the Levites; Shemaiah the son of Hasshub, the son of Azrikam, the
son of Hashabiah, of the sons of Merari; 
\v 15 And Bakbakkar, Heresh, and Galal, and Mattaniah the son of Micah, the
son of Zichri, the son of Asaph; 
\v 16 And Obadiah the son of Shemaiah, the son of Galal, the son of Jeduthun,
and Berechiah the son of Asa, the son of Elkanah, that dwelt in the villages
of the Netophathites. 
\v 17 And the porters \add were,\add* Shallum, and Akkub, and Talmon, and
Ahiman, and their brethren: Shallum \add was\add* the chief; 
\v 18 Who hitherto \add waited\add* in the king’s gate eastward: they were
porters in the companies of the children of Levi. 
\v 19 And Shallum the son of Kore, the son of Ebiasaph, the son of Korah, and
his brethren, of the house of his father, the Korahites, \add were\add* over
the work of the service, keepers of the gates of the tabernacle: and their
fathers, \add being\add* over the host of the LORD, \add were\add* keepers of
the entry. 
\v 20 And Phinehas the son of Eleazar was the ruler over them in time past, 
\add and\add* the Lord \add was\add* with him. 
\v 21 \add And\add* Zechariah the son of Meshelemiah \add was\add* porter of
the door of the tabernacle of the congregation. 
\v 22 All these \add which were\add* chosen to be porters in the gates were
two hundred and twelve. These were reckoned by their genealogy in their
villages, whom David and Samuel the seer did ordain in their set office. 
\v 23 So they and their children \add had\add* the oversight of the gates of
the house of the Lord, \add namely,\add* the house of the tabernacle, by
wards. 
\v 24 In four quarters were the porters, toward the east, west, north, and
south. 
\v 25 And their brethren, \add which were\add* in their villages, \add were
\add* to come after seven days from time to time with them. 
\v 26 For these Levites, the four chief porters, were in \add their
\add* set office, and were over the chambers and treasuries of the house of
God.
\p
\v 27 And they lodged round about the house of God, because the charge 
\add was\add* upon them, and the opening thereof every morning \add pertained
\add* to them. 
\v 28 And \add certain\add* of them had the charge of the ministering vessels,
that they should bring them in and out by tale. 
\v 29 \add Some\add* of them also \add were\add* appointed to oversee the
vessels, and all the instruments of the sanctuary, and the fine flour, and the
wine, and the oil, and the frankincense, and the spices. 
\v 30 And \add some\add* of the sons of the priests made the ointment of the
spices. 
\v 31 And Mattithiah, \add one\add* of the Levites, who \add was\add* the
firstborn of Shallum the Korahite, had the set office over the things that
were made in the pans. 
\v 32 And \add other\add* of their brethren, of the sons of the Kohathites, 
\add were\add* over the shewbread, to prepare \add it\add* every sabbath. 
\v 33 And these \add are\add* the singers, chief of the fathers of the
Levites, \add who remaining\add* in the chambers \add were\add* free: for they
were employed in that work day and night. 
\v 34 These chief fathers of the Levites \add were\add* chief throughout their
generations; these dwelt at Jerusalem.
\p
\v 35 And in Gibeon dwelt the father of Gibeon, Jehiel, whose wife’s name 
\add was\add* Maachah: 
\v 36 And his firstborn son Abdon, then Zur, and Kish, and Baal, and Ner, and
Nadab, 
\v 37 And Gedor, and Ahio, and Zechariah, and Mikloth. 
\v 38 And Mikloth begat Shimeam. And they also dwelt with their brethren at
Jerusalem, over against their brethren. 
\v 39 And Ner begat Kish; and Kish begat Saul; and Saul begat Jonathan, and
Malchi-shua, and Abinadab, and Esh-baal. 
\v 40 And the son of Jonathan \add was\add* Merib- baal: and Merib-baal begat
Micah. 
\v 41 And the sons of Micah \add were,\add* Pithon, and Melech, and Tahrea, 
\add and Ahaz. \add*
\v 42 And Ahaz begat Jarah; and Jarah begat Alemeth, and Azmaveth, and Zimri;
and Zimri begat Moza; 
\v 43 And Moza begat Binea; and Rephaiah his son, Eleasah his son, Azel his
son. 
\v 44 And Azel had six sons, whose names \add are\add* these, Azrikam,
Bocheru, and Ishmael, and Sheariah, and Obadiah, and Hanan: these \add were
\add* the sons of Azel.
\c 10
\p
\v 1 Now the Philistines fought against Israel; and the men of Israel fled
from before the Philistines, and fell down slain in mount Gilboa. 
\v 2 And the Philistines followed hard after Saul, and after his sons; and the
Philistines slew Jonathan, and Abinadab, and Malchi-shua, the sons of Saul. 
\v 3 And the battle went sore against Saul, and the archers hit him, and he
was wounded of the archers. 
\v 4 Then said Saul to his armourbearer, Draw thy sword, and thrust me through
therewith; lest these uncircumcised come and abuse me. But his armourbearer
would not; for he was sore afraid. So Saul took a sword, and fell upon it. 
\v 5 And when his armourbearer saw that Saul was dead, he fell likewise on the
sword, and died. 
\v 6 So Saul died, and his three sons, and all his house died together. 
\v 7 And when all the men of Israel that \add were\add* in the valley saw that
they fled, and that Saul and his sons were dead, then they forsook their
cities, and fled: and the Philistines came and dwelt in them.
\p
\v 8 And it came to pass on the morrow, when the Philistines came to strip the
slain, that they found Saul and his sons fallen in mount Gilboa. 
\v 9 And when they had stripped him, they took his head, and his armour, and
sent into the land of the Philistines round about, to carry tidings unto their
idols, and to the people. 
\v 10 And they put his armour in the house of their gods, and fastened his
head in the temple of Dagon.
\p
\v 11 And when all Jabesh-gilead heard all that the Philistines had done to
